o<slotcut> sub
  (slot cutting, load tool and set feed first, then use like so:)
  (1[x1] 2[y1] 3[x2] 4[y2] #5[width] 6[depth] 7[safety height] 8[tool dia])

#<x1> = #1
#<y1> = #2
#<x2> = #3
#<y2> = #4
#<width> = #5
#<depth> = #6 (=-0.5)
#<z_safe> = #7
#<> = #

#10=[#<width>/2] (radius)
#11=[[atan [#<y2>-#<y1>]/[#<x2>-#1]] + 180] ("backward" direction)
#12=[#11 + 90] ("right" side direction)
#13=[#10 * [cos [#11]]]
#14=[#10 * [sin [#11]]]
#15=[#10 * [cos [#12]]]
#16=[#10 * [sin [#12]]]
g0 z#<z_safe>
g0 x[#1+#13+#15] y[#<y1>+#14+#16]
g41 g0x[#1+#15] y[#<y1>+#16]
#17=[#8/2] (depth per cut is half tool dia)
#18=[#<z_safe>-#17] (z)
(down toward the specified depth a bit at a time)
o201 while [#18 GT #<depth>]
g1 x[#<x2>+#15] y[#<y2>+#16] z#18
g3 x[#<x2>-#15] y[#<y2>-#16] r#10
g1 x[#1-#15] y[#<y1>-#16]
g3 x[#1+#15] y[#<y1>+#16] r#10
#18=[#18-#17]
o201 endwhile
(down to the actual depth and one more cut)
g1 x[#<x2>+#15] y[#<y2>+#16] z#<depth>
g3 x[#<x2>-#15] y[#<y2>-#16] r#10
g1 x[#1-#15] y[#<y1>-#16]
g3 x[#1+#15] y[#<y1>+#16] r#10
g1 x[#<x2>+#15] y[#<y2>+#16]
g0 z#<z_safe>
g40
o<slotcut> endsub